# Backend Architecture

- Keep controllers thin; orchestrate only request parsing and response mapping.
- Place business rules in services/use-cases, not in controllers/routes.
- Keep data access in repositories or dedicated persistence layers.
- Use typed request/response contracts and validated DTOs/schemas.
- Handle errors explicitly with consistent logging and status mapping.
- Avoid cross-layer imports that bypass service boundaries.
